description.narrative: 4,000 families benefitted from UNICEF-supported parenting helpline services. Moreover, 964 parents/caregivers benefitted from the roll-out of parenting programmesdelivered by trained master trainers and facilitators, using evidence-informed training curriculumswith gender-responsive content and delivery methods tailored to various audiences. Around 1,800youth were equipped with life skills to help them prevent violence, including GBV, while 174 youth were also provided with trauma-informed counselling services using sports and theater for development approaches as entry points for engagement. Approximately166,331 persons were reached by UNICEF-supported C4D initiatives, aimed at challenging the social acceptance of violence and encouraging reporting and help-seeking behaviour. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
